        </disp-formula>
        <p>where <italic toggle="yes">R</italic><sub>1</sub> and <italic toggle="yes">R</italic><sub>2</sub> stand for the number of replicates in condition 1 and 2, respectively.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec id="SEC2-1-2">
        <title>Segmentation model</title>
        <p>We consider <italic toggle="yes">D</italic> changepoints <italic toggle="yes">τ<sub>1</sub>&lt;…&lt; τ<sub>D</sub></italic> within the range 1 and <italic toggle="yes">n</italic> – 1. These changepoints correspond to unknown positions along the genome where a shift in the mean of the per-base log<sub>2</sub>-FC (eq: 2) is observed. We adopt the convention that <italic toggle="yes">τ</italic><sub>0</sub>= 0 and <italic toggle="yes">τ</italic><sub>|</sub><italic toggle="yes"><sub>τ</sub></italic><sub>|</sub> = <italic toggle="yes">n</italic>. These changepoints define |<italic toggle="yes">τ</italic>| = <italic toggle="yes">D</italic> + 1 distinct segments. The <italic toggle="yes">j</italic>th segment includes the data <inline-formula><tex-math id="M0003" notation="LaTeX">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
